**Case-study-only or page-specific styles:** Some pages link extra CSS (`assets/css/spring.css`, etc.) or use a scoped `<style>` block (e.g. `quickbite.html`). When extending the system in Figma, add a **“Case study / module”** page for optional blocks (tabs, icon grids, galleries) that are not global.

## Asset handling

- **Images:** `assets/img/` (project heroes, thumbnails under `assets/img/main images/`, per-project folders).
- **Favicon:** `assets/img/favicon.svg`.
- **No bundler:** reference paths relative to site root in HTML/CSS.
- When Figma MCP provides **localhost asset URLs**, use them directly per MCP guidance; then save exports under the appropriate `assets/img/<Project>/` folder and update HTML `src`.

## Icon system

- **Font Awesome 6.4** is injected in `PortfolioApp.injectHead()` in `components.js` (CDN). Markup uses `<i class="fas fa-*">` (and variants).
- IMPORTANT: Prefer **FA classes already used on the site** for consistency. Do not add new icon packs unless the design explicitly requires it.

## Styling approach

- **Global:** `assets/css/style.css` (+ `assets/css/cursor.css` for cursor).
- **Methodology:** plain CSS, semantic layout classes, CSS variables for theming.
- **Responsive:** media queries in `style.css` (e.g. `.case-section` padding, grids collapsing to one column, mobile header visibility).
- IMPORTANT: **Never hardcode theme colors in new CSS** — use `var(--bg-color)`, `var(--text-color)`, `var(--accent-color)`, `var(--border-color)`, `var(--secondary-text)` so dark mode stays correct.

## Figma MCP integration (Cursor + plugin-figma-figma)

Use these steps for every Figma-driven change (adapt names to your MCP tool list):

1. Fetch structured context for the **exact node(s)** to implement (e.g. `get_design_context`).
2. If the payload is too large, fetch metadata for the file/frame, then request only the needed nodes.
3. Take a **screenshot** of the target node for visual reference (e.g. `get_screenshot`).
4. Download assets from the MCP asset endpoint when needed; place under `assets/img/` and wire in HTML.
5. **Translate** MCP output: default generations are often React + Tailwind. For this repo, output **semantic HTML** and **CSS** using the tokens above; reuse existing class names where they match.
6. Validate layout and spacing against the screenshot at desktop and mobile widths.

## Implementation rules

- IMPORTANT: Treat MCP-generated React/Tailwind as **design reference**, not final code style.
- Prefer **extending `style.css`** for shared patterns; use **page-specific CSS files** or scoped `<style>` only when the pattern is unique to one case study.
- Reuse **layout builders** in `layout-components.js` when changing chrome (header, sidebar, footer, next projects); content stays in each HTML file’s `#page-specific-content`.
- Project metadata (title, tags, links) for project pages: `PortfolioApp.projectList` and `pageData` in `components.js` must stay in sync with visible content when applicable.
- Respect **accessibility:** preserve meaningful image `alt` text, heading order, and focus styles; interactive elements need keyboard support if you add new controls.

