## Building a matching Figma library (manual — no `.fig` export from the agent)

Use this checklist to **create** the design system inside Figma (variables + components). The code above is the source of truth; update Figma when CSS changes.

1. **Variables (collections):** Create `Theme / Light` and `Theme / Dark` modes with the color table above; add `accent/hover` and semantic fills (placeholder grays, accent tints).
2. **Typography styles:** Montserrat; create the text styles listed under Typography.
3. **Effect styles:** Card hover — optional shadow or rely on border `2px` accent on `.image-container` / `.next-project-img`.
4. **Components:** Frame components for `Nav link`, `Nav home pill`, `Filter chip`, `Sidebar tag`, `Visit CTA`, `Back pill`, `Project tile (default/hover)`, `Case section header`, `Case table cell row`, `CTA pill primary/secondary`, `Footer default/green`.
5. **Layouts:** Desktop: sidebar ~30% / main ~70% (see `.sidebar` / `.right-panel`). Mobile: follow breakpoints in `style.css` (~1200px, ~900px, ~600px).

This gives you a **Figma design system that mirrors the live site**; the Cursor rules above keep future implementations aligned.
